Preparatory committee formed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- A national preparatory committee of Peru was formed to commemorate the 87th birthday of the President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chairman of the Peru-Korea Institute of Culture and Friendship was elected chairman of the preparatory committee and general secretary of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, general secretary of the Socialist Party of Peru, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru and general secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland) were elected vice-chairmen at the inaugural meeting on Monday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They set a commemoration month from February 15 to April 15 and decided to organize colorful functions including a meeting, a lecture meeting, a remembering session and a seminar on achievements.

Kim Jong Il's work published in Pakistan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's work "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully Through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation" was published in book form by the Afzal Publishing House of Pakistan on Feb. 11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
  Preface of the book says that Kim Jong Il has strengthened the Workers' Party of Korea into a Juche type revolutionary party and the Korean People's Army into invincible revolutionary armed forces and led Korean socialism centered on the people along the road of victory by creditably applying the Juche idea for 3 decades.   It stresses that he energetically leads the struggle of the Korean people to achieve independent and peaceful reunification of the country through the great unity of the entire nation.

Cambodian King gives reception on Kim Jong Il's birthday
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk gave a reception on Feb. 16 on the occasion of  the 57th birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.   The King said in his speech that February 16 is the most significant and auspicious day for the Cambodian people.   He wholeheartedly wished Kim Jong Il on his 57th birthday a long life in good health and success in accomplishing the noble cause of leading the Korean people to victory.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
  The respected Marshal Kim Jong Il is the greatest historic hero who is identical with the great Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, he said, and went on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kim Jong Il has energetically and wisely led  the party, the state and the army of Korea for 30 odd years to turn Korea into a great powerful nation which the world people envy and build the Korean People's Army into a matchless army that can defeat any formidable enemy.   He is now wisely leading the struggle to build a great powerful nation, stronger and more prosperous.   The King extended the warmest respect and wholehearted reverence and greetings to the Marshal.

Shameless and preposterous remarks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- The South Korean "Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade" in a recent "television interview" span out a shameless and preposterous rigmarole about "engagement policy" towards the North Korea and "beneficial and non-beneficial offer." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Commenting on this, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun today observes:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The "engagement policy" on the lips of the South Korean authorities is a variety of what they called "sunshine policy". It is, in essence, a pseudo policy of reunification utterly contrary to the three principles of national reunification, independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity. Therefore, it is no more than a wild dream.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is the height of shamelessness for them to "engage" he north which they branded as a "major enemy", while labeling the people calling for reconciliation with the north and  reunification as "enemy-benefiting elements."
   And, it is disgustful for the South Korean authorities to talk about "beneficial and non-beneficial offer" to somebody at a time when they are busying themselves with begging for money to save their economy from total collapse.
   If they do not stop making such maladroit and shameful remarks they will have to pay dearly for this.

Secret strife between two rivals
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- The relationship between the present chief executive of South Korea and Prime Minister Kim Jong Pil is getting worse because of divergent views of the two potential rivals on the "constitutional revision" for "parliamentary system of government", according to reports from Seoul.   When Kim Jong Pil visited "Chongwadae" to report results of his foreign trip of 11 days and 10 nights, the chief executive met him for 30 minutes only.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As regards this, the chief of information of "Chongwadae" said the issue of "constitutional revision" for the "parliamentary system of government" was not mentioned at all at the conversation.   The 2 rivals quarreled with each other  over the issue even when they were far away from each other before Kim Jong Pil's arrival in Seoul, drawing public attention.   This shows that contradiction of the present "coalition government" is getting worse.

Realistic proposal for opening epochal phase
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- Political parties and organizations of different countries published statements supporting the proposal of a joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Maurice Bishop Patriotic Movement of Grenada said that the proposal is a most realistic one to open an epochal phase for the reunification of Korea through national independence and great unity.   The Ecuadorian Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea and the Guayaquil and Cuenca committees under it, the Ecuadorian Cultural Institute for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Voluntad Publishing House in a joint statement strongly demanded that the South Korean authorities take urgent practical steps for discontinuing "cooperation" with outside forces, stopping joint military exercises with them, repealing the "National Security Law" and providing pro-reunification patriots and organisations with the freedom of reunification movement and activities and approach reunification-orientated wide-ranging dialogue.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Socialist Unionist Party of Syria said that wide-ranging dialogue between the north and south of Korea including authorities should be held without fail and that political parties, organizations and personages of all social standings in South Korea should extensively develop independent non-governmental dialogue and reunification movement.   The c.c., the Communist Party-KPMI (R) of Sweden said that the initiative for talks on the three principles of national reunification is most just and timely, adding that the South Korean authorities should no longer play a stooge of the U.S. imperialists.   The Communist Party (Red Motherland), the National Reconciliation Movement, the Revolutionary Socialist Party and 6 other political parties of Peru in a joint statement strongly demanded that the United States stop the moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and unleash a second Korean war, honestly implement the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework and withdraw its troops from South Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They also called upon political parties, organizations and people of all countries of the world to make efforts for the realization of the proposal of the joint meeting.   Hamilton Green, leader of the Good Green Guyana, in a statement said that if dialogue between the north and south is to be held truly for reunification, practical steps for removing stumbling blocks in realizing dialogue should be taken in South Korea before anything else.
